main event: A civilian observer reported seeing a bright, pale green object in the sky on November 6, 1966.
interesting points: The object had no verifiable shape and appeared larger than a star., Its color alternated between green and blue., The object was visible for over an hour and showed a steady flight path from northwest to southeast with no erratic movement., The observer used binoculars and noted the weather was clear., There were no reports of sound associated with the object.
sighted object: A brightly brilliant, pale green object
witness description: The witness is a civilian, age 41+, who is a spokesperson for a group that includes her husband and neighbors who also witnessed the sightings.
